    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a25b6785_0496df03",
        "filename": "client/crash_report_database_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 872,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-17T22:57:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This method should also delete any attachments for the report.\n\nIt\u0027s possible for the database or it\u0027s metadata to become corrupt and leak reports or attachments https://bugs.chromium.org/p/crashpad/issues/detail?id\u003d66. You could implement CleanDatabase() to clean up reports and attachments that don\u0027t have valid metadata.\n\nAs an optional alternative to implementing these features in the Windows database, you could have your application use the generic database implementation instead by adding a gn arg \"crashpad_use_generic_database\" that causes crash_report_database_generic.cc to be built instead of crash_report_database_win.cc. I don\u0027t think we\u0027d want to do that automatically for all Crashpad users because each application would need to think about how to transition from the old database format to the new one, but it might be okay for your application to e.g. just delete your old database and start a new one.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 872,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 872,
        "endChar": 52
      },
      "revId": "6f76d0f6522062f97e94c471b6cde40659ef39d7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7ef98df4_a7e12578",
        "filename": "client/crash_report_database_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 872,
      "author": {
        "id": 1429565
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-19T20:01:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I added function Metadata::CleanDatabase() and CrashReportDatabaseWin::CleanDatabase() to sync reports and metadata. Also added deletion of attachments in this method.",
      "parentUuid": "a25b6785_0496df03",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 872,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 872,
        "endChar": 52
      },
      "revId": "6f76d0f6522062f97e94c471b6cde40659ef39d7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
